Service Catalog
Catalog Fulfillments are the pieces of automation that make processing user-generated requests simple. They ensure service requests are accomplished efficiently and effectively, and customers receive the services they request.
Each catalog item is assigned to only one catalog fulfillment, but fulfillments can be associated with multiple catalog items.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions

A catalog fulfillment is a flow that you assign to a catalog item. You can install predefined fulfillments or create customizable ones inside or outside of Service Catalog.
Watch the video to see how to accelerate service automation with catalog fulfillments:

SvcCatalogFulfillmentFlow shows the fulfillment’s name and description, explaining what it does when it runs.

A SvcCatalogFulfillFlowItem is a child object that describes an input variable and its valid data. You define these variables in the catalog item builder or ask customers to do so.
All constants and additional questions are saved in a custom catalog fulfillment. A catalog item calls the associated catalog fulfillment, adding one question-answer string to the IsAdditionalQuestionsInputVariable inputs of the associated fulfillments.
